parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to be inoperable
transmission fails to maintain gear selection
transmission jumps out of gear when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the transmission to slip, leading to loss of control and accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag Deployment in Frontal Collisions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in severe frontal collisions can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to occupants, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in frontal collisions
resulting in potential injuries or fatalities to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwarranted airbag deployment can cause unnecessary injuries, distractions, and disruptions to occupants, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: even in minor collisions or bumps
causing unexpected and potentially harmful consequences.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Front Disc Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of front disc brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: vibration or shimmy when brakes are applied
squealing or grinding noises when braking.
